                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">1</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">The Congregation Beth Elohim of\n                    <placeName>Charleston</placeName>.</p>\n            <p>No 6 full price</p>\n            <p>The attention of the Jewish Public being directed to the<lb/> movement of this\n                congregation, we beg leave to lay before them<lb/> a statistical and comprehensive\n                sketch of the part and parsing<lb/> events which have agitated and are now agitating\n                this body.</p>\n            <p>At the period when the <persName>Rev Y Posnanski</persName> was elected for a\n                probationary term of two years Hazan of the<lb/> K. K. B. E. it was one of the most\n                Orthodox, Religious, &amp; <sic>Charatable</sic><lb/> in the <placeName>United\n                    States</placeName>.—after the expiration of one year. The Congregation<lb/> in\n                consideration of his ardent zeal in the cause of our holy Religion<lb/> his piety\n                and conformation to all the laws both Mosaic and<lb/> Rabbinical, Elected him for\n                life.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">As soon as this event took place a course diametrically<lb/>\n                opposite was immediately pursued by <persName>Mr Poznanski</persName>, which<lb/>\n                was the cause of the disastrous outbreak in <date>1841</date>, when upwards<lb/> of\n                Forty of the <del>oldest</del> most <sic>consciensious</sic> and <del>most</del>\n                strictly conservative members were<lb/> scrupulously compelled to <del>resign</del>\n                withdraw, (among whom were<lb/> the founders of the congregation) and to leave in\n                the power of<lb/> its rulers not only that Sacred Edifice which was identified\n                with<lb/> many Holy associations, but <sic>but</sic> were denied any participation\n                in the management of the Kyrankyamits<lb/> Fund to which they had largely\n                contributed until it had<lb/> accumulated to the Sum of $25.000. the Interest of\n                which<lb/> was appropriated to support the very individual who by his<lb/> arbitrary\n                and anti Jewish Conduct cause another dispersion<lb/> in\n                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>, and depriving the aged supporters of the\n                Congregation<lb/> their Venerable matrons and their children, not only of a\n                place<lb/> of worship but also of the <sic>priveledges</sic> of Sepulture, for\n                imme-<lb/>-diately upon their withdrawal, the constitution of the KKBE.<lb/> was\n                amended as follows “Any Subscriber Yehid, or member<lb/> of this Congregation, male\n                or Female who shall habitually<lb/> attend <hi rend=\"underline\">Divine</hi> service\n                at any other place of worship within<lb/> the city than that of the KKB.E. or\n                subscribe there to as<lb/> members or Yeshidim shall be charged annually One\n                Hundred<lb/> Dollars” We do not deem any comment necessary.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Congregation remained in a lethargic state until<lb/> its second\n                Revolution in <date>1843</date>, which involved it in an</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p38912b3q/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
