                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">3</p>\n            <p>opposite extremes originated as follows. The <persName>Revd Dr<lb/> Eckman</persName>\n                from repealed conversations <del>from</del> on his first arrival<lb/> with\n                    <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> and from personal observations\n                afterwards,<lb/> found that all positive religion <del>had fallen into Decay</del>\n                was rejected<lb/> no religious instruction was communicated in the synagogue<lb/>\n                (as <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> did not lecture) prophecy was denied,\n                hence<lb/> the denial of all that is <del>Dogmatical</del> Doctrinal and National.\n                The<lb/> non observance of the Law not only passively connived at,<lb/> but he\n                exposed some Laws that might offend our<lb/> modern delicacy, to the view of his\n                adherents the more<lb/> effectually to prove there was no <sic>nescessity</sic> for\n                observing them<lb/> his request to <persName>Dr. E.</persName> to preach against the\n                    <sic>Rabbies</sic> and<lb/> all observances whither Biblical or Rabbinical and\n                his acknowledgment to him<lb/> that it was of no consequence where the bible came\n                from<lb/> convinced <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> of <persName>Mr\n                    Posnanskis</persName>\n                <del>rank</del> daring Infidelity,<lb/> as <persName>Mr Newman</persName> calls it.\n                    <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> kept silent<lb/>\n                <sic>untill</sic>\n                <date>Yom Kipur</date> when <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> was called to<lb/>\n                take part in the sacred functions of that day. This <persName>Dr<lb/>\n                    Eckman</persName>, as an honest man, could not consent to<lb/> and\n                    <sic>and</sic> privately remonstrated with <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> on\n                the great<lb/> crime of Profanation. <persName>Mr Poznanski</persName> replied,\n                that<lb/> he not only did not believe <del>the <date>Yom Kipur</date></del> these\n                prayers,<lb/> but he detested them, whereupon <persName>Dr Eckman</persName><lb/>\n                denounced him to the Parnass. Not only as an Infidel<lb/> but inimically disposed to\n                the very Institution of<lb/> Judaism, and positively refused to take any part<lb/>\n                in the service of that day. The Personal friends<lb/> of <persName>Mr\n                    Posnanski</persName> immediately arrayed themselves in<lb/> open hostilities\n                against <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> and have waged them <sic>untill</sic> the\n                present<lb/> time. The great Injustice of this <del>course</del> persecution being\n                so<lb/> evident to the public, and <persName>Dr. Eckmans</persName> straight<lb/>\n                German course in the cause of Religion and Truth<lb/> has drawn to his Standard of\n                True Faith a large<lb/> number of the most respectable and intelligent members of\n                the congregation*<lb/> The Radical or <persName>Posnanski</persName> party numbers\n                exactly Eighteen<lb/>\n                <del>*among whom we mention <persName>Mr Joshua Lazarus</persName> the Prest of the\n                    congregation and <persName>Mr M C Mordecai<add>?</add></persName>,<lb/> both so\n                    honorably named in your last number.</del></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p38912b3q/canvas/p5"
