                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">4</p>\n            <p>the Conservative party Fifteen members and four Congregators<lb/> the remaining\n                    <del>8 or 9 members</del> Eight or nine, are<lb/> indisposed to take any part in\n                Congregational affairs.<lb/>\n                <del>altho we believe they convinced of the fallacious<lb/> ideas they have recently\n                    entertained on Religious subjects.</del></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The public denunciation of the creed By <persName>Dr\n                    Eckman</persName> at the Tabernacle<lb/> Lecture Room some weeks ago; as being\n                anti Jewish, and as<lb/> having been surreptitiously introduced in the\n                Synagogue,<lb/> gave publicity to the following facts viz.</p>\n            <p>The Building Committee received instructions from the<lb/> congregation to have “Our\n                Creed <hi rend=\"underline\">translated</hi> and placed<lb/> in the synagogue; and\n                recommended the <del>services</del> assistance of their<lb/> Hazan the\n                    <persName>Rev. G Posnanski</persName> for that purpose, the committee<lb/>\n                accordingly informed that Gentn of the wishes of the<lb/> congregation, to which he\n                assented, and <del>they subsequently</del> this prepared<lb/>\n                <del>received from him</del> creed was placed in the synagogue as Our „the\n                Maimonidian” creed<lb/>\n                <del>that which is now placed in the synagogue</del> It contains<lb/> like that of\n                    <persName>Maimonides</persName> thirteen articles <del>of I</del> and<lb/>\n                purports to be “Elements of Jewish Faith.”</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">This committee, with the exception of <persName>Mr\n                    Posnanski</persName>, with fearless <sic>magninimity</sic>, have<lb/> recently\n                expressed, that they have no <sic>pretentions</sic> to<lb/> Biblical or Rabbinical\n                Lore, that they never supposed<lb/> that <del>it</del> this creed aimed a blow at\n                the very vitals of Judaism,<lb/> they received <del>this creed</del> it in full\n                faith of its really<lb/> being, that which the congregation requested them to<lb/>\n                procure viz a translation of “<hi rend=\"underline\">our</hi> the Maimonidian<lb/>\n                Creed and if it <hi rend=\"underline\">were</hi> any thing else, it was <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">not</hi><lb/> the acknowledged creed of the congregation;<lb/>\n                a Public meeting of the Sunday School attached<lb/> to the K K B.E. under the sole\n                control of the Ladies<lb/> of the Congregation, was convened soon after this\n                and<lb/> the creed which had hitherto been taught, was rejected<lb/> and forever\n                expelled from school <del>by a vote of 25 to 3</del>.<lb/> It would not be out of\n                place here to answer <del>“C” a</del><lb/> the objections <del>which</del> of “C” in\n                the last “Occident” to<lb/> the views</p>"
                  },
