                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">5</p>\n            <p><persName>Mr Newman</persName> takes (on his <del>anima</del> criticism of this\n                creed) of the substitution of the Divine<lb/> Law handed by\n                    <persName>moses</persName> to our Fathers” for the Universal<lb/> believe (and\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">correct translation of</hi>\n                <persName>Maimonides</persName>). “that the<lb/> Law was <del>given</del> delivered\n                unto <persName>Moses</persName> by God,” <del>I</del><lb/> The only article of Faith\n                necessary for any believer<lb/> is that of <add>תורה מן השמים</add> if this is\n                admitted <del>then</del> the<lb/> other two propose by “<persName>Albo</persName>,”\n                and the Twelve according to<lb/>\n                <persName>Maimonides</persName>, follow of themselves, as the<del>re</del>\n                whole<lb/> Bible is there acknowledged to be given by God<lb/>\n                <del>to</del> and all the contents binding, but this very<lb/> article is distorted\n                and rendered inane by<lb/> the alteration introduced in article 8<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                    >th</hi> where<lb/> instead of the Universal belief that the Law was<lb/>\n                delivered to <persName>Moses</persName> by God, it is in <persName>Mr\n                    Posnanskis</persName><lb/> creed only considered as a divine Law delivered<lb/>\n                by <persName>Moses</persName> unto our Fathers—now a “divine<lb/> Law delivered by\n                    <persName>Moses</persName> may mean no more<lb/>\n                <del>than</del> and stand no higher than, a “Divine Poem<lb/> By\n                    <persName>Milton</persName>, a Divine Hymn, by <persName>Dr\n                Watts</persName><lb/> “Divine Service by an incompetent Lay man<lb/> or a Divine\n                Comedy by “<persName>Dante</persName>,” the word<lb/> “Divine” is of less import\n                than “Sacred”, and<lb/> “divine and sacred less than “Holy”. The draft<lb/> of the\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">Translator</hi> may easily be <sic>percured</sic> by<lb/>\n                comparing Article 9<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> which immediately follows<lb/> when\n                instead of the Positive and emphatic assertion<lb/>\n                <del>that</del> of <persName>Maimonides</persName> viz we believe with a\n                firm/perfect faith, that<lb/> this Law will never be changed or altered, and<lb/>\n                that there will be <hi rend=\"underline\">no other Law Given</hi> by the<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">Creator</hi> Blessed be his name, he simply states<lb/> that we\n                believe the divine Law will never be<lb/> altered or changed”, he has expunged or\n                forgot<lb/> to translate, what we so <hi rend=\"underline\">very much</hi> want to\n                hear<lb/> viz that <hi rend=\"underline\">the Creator blessed be his name, never\n                    will</hi><lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">give any other Law.</hi><lb/> “C” also states that Mr.</p>"
