                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">6</p>\n            <p><persName>Poznanski</persName> “never advocated doctrines that conflicted with\n                the<lb/> cardinal principles of our religion.” It is not difficult<lb/> to infer\n                what a man's moral and religious principles<lb/> are when his own words and actions\n                sufficiently<lb/> indicate them.</p>\n            <p>Firstly—in his discussion with <persName>Dr Raphall</persName>, when asked<lb/> if he\n                believed in the Bible in the Law &amp; the Prophets<lb/> he in the presence of both\n                Organizations replied after a long hesitation Y-e-s <del>with qualifications\n                    some</del><lb/> several of his <del>friends</del> own congregation inferring\n                from<lb/> his evasion and long consideration, that he did not fully believe</p>\n            <p>\n                <del>Secondly—His unbelief in the coming of the personal messiah<lb/> the,\n                        Ressurection<add>?</add> and in the prayers which<lb/> and “that God gave\n                    the law,” <add>?</add> his creed”</del>\n            </p>\n            <p>Secondly <del>his disbelief in</del> the non obligation of observance of the\n                ceremonial and<lb/> Rabbinical Laws as <add>?</add> to <persName>Dr\n                    Eckman</persName><lb/> and <persName>Mr Newman</persName>,”</p>\n            <p><del>We also understand “C” is the author of the Petition</del><lb/> and Lastly his\n                extreme inconsistent course viz coming to <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> as\n                a pious and orthodox mosaic &amp; Rabbinical Hazan,<lb/> and in a short time\n                afterwards subverting our <hi rend=\"underline\">faith</hi><lb/> by introducing into\n                the synagogue, one of his own<lb/> manufacture which his replete with Infidelity\n                &amp;<lb/> Irreligion”</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The <persName>Posnanski</persName> parties finding themselves\n                reduced<lb/> in the last Ten Years from over One Hundred voting members<lb/> to only\n                Eighteen, and destruction approaching from exposure of<lb/> their leader by\n                    <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> determined as a last<lb/> resort they being in\n                the majority on the Board of<lb/> Trustees, to transmit a petition to the Board\n                with<lb/> the request that <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> should resign as they did\n                not think <del>men</del> suited their needs<add>?</add>. This<lb/> Petition, Signed\n                by the Eighteen members, was<lb/> accordingly sent in, and a resolution passed<lb/>\n                by a note of 4 to 3 that <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> should comply<lb/> with the\n                weeks of the petitions, a contra petition<lb/> was also sent to the Board signed by\n                Fifteen members</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
